rotection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Havard was born about 1274, in Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1274–":"umbes 1274–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1274–Male":"1274–Surnud","1300":"1300","1274":"1274","about 1274":"umbes 1274",",Breconshire,Wales.":"Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1274–":"noin 1274–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1274–Male":"1274–Kuollut","1300":"1300","1274":"1274","about 1274":"noin 1274",",Breconshire,Wales.":"Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1274–":"environ 1274–Décédé","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1274–Male":"1274–Décédé","1300":"1300","1274":"1274","about 1274":"environ 1274",",Breconshire,Wales.":"Breconshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Havard est né environ 1274, à Breconshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1274–":"um 1274–Verstorben","1300–Female":"1300–Verstorben","1274–Male":"1274–Verstorben","1300":"1300","1274":"1274","about 1274":"um 1274",",Breconshire,Wales.":"Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"William Havard wurde um 1274 in Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"about 1274–":"about 1274–Desede","1300–Female":"1300–Desede","1274–Male":"1274–Desede","1300":"1300","1274":"1274","about 1274":"about 1274",",Breconshire,Wales.":"Breconshire, Pays de Galles, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"about 1274–":"1274 körül–elhunyt","1300–Female":"1300–elhunyt","1274–Male":"1274–elhunyt","1300":"1300","1274":"1274","ab